Definition: deeply absorbed in thought
Example: as distant and bemused as a professor listening to the prattling of his freshman class; lost in thought; a preoccupied frown
Synonyms: lost, p, preoccupied, noun, cognition, preoccupancy, deeply, absorbed, in, thought, as, distant, and, a, professor, listening, to, the, prattling, of, his, freshman, class, frown
Category: adj.all
